    "This level of differences in human and AI scores is typically considered large enough to be concerned, and further investigation is warranted (as per Williamson et al., 2012).",
    "Interestingly, the overall QWK for these two tasks was about 0.78 on average, indicating acceptable agreement.",
    "However, the tasks that showed higher human and AI agreement had low mean SMDs.",
    "Generally, when the overall model evaluation shows high levels of agreement and prediction accuracy (McCaffrey et al., 2024), there tend to be no subgroup differences (McCaffrey et al., 2022).",
    "This was found in the next challenge in 2023 when NCES/IES hosted a challenge to explore the accuracy and fairness of scoring open-ended responses to the NAEP Math assessment for fourth and eighth grade."
